#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5229
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b; (Export to K3b Project)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b; (Exportera till K3b-projekt)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the K3b Export Plugin"
msgstr "Skärmbild av insticksmodulen K3b-export"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5244
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_export_k3b;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Saves all sections between markers into a separate file and creates a K3b "
"project file. After having successfully written all files it is possible to "
"start <ulink url=\"&url_k3b;\">K3b</ulink> and burn the result to an audio "
"&CD;. This is useful for splitting a file with a recording that consists of "
"several parts, which are separated by labels, and then burn it to an audio "
"&CD; with multiple tracks, including &CD; text meta data which is extracted "
"from the descriptions of the labels."
msgstr ""
"Sparar alla sektioner mellan markörer i separata filer och skapar en K3b-"
"projektfil. Efter att ha skrivit alla filer med lyckat resultat är det "
"möjligt att starta <ulink url=\"&url_k3b;\">K3b</ulink> och bränna "
"resultatet på en ljud-cd. Det är användbart för att dela upp en fil med en "
"inspelning som består av flera delar, som är åtskilda med markörer, och "
"därefter bränna en ljud-cd med flera spår, inklusive cd-text metadata, som "
"extraheras från markörernas beskrivningar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"(This plugin is internally using the <link linkend=\"plugin_sect_saveblocks"
"\" endterm=\"plugin_title_saveblocks\"></link> plugin.)"
msgstr ""
"(Insticksmodulen använder internt insticksmodulen <link linkend="
"\"plugin_sect_saveblocks\" endterm=\"plugin_title_saveblocks\"></link>)."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5275 index.docbook:6503
#, no-c-format
msgid "pattern"
msgstr "mönster"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pattern that will be used for detecting title and artist from the label at "
"the start of a section. It supports the following wildcards which will be "
"replaced by the corresponding content when creating the &CD; text meta data:"
msgstr ""
"Ett mönster som kommer att användas för att detektera titel och artist från "
"etiketten i början på en sektion. Det stöder följande jokertecken, som "
"ersätts av motsvarande innehåll när metadata för cd-text skapas:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5289 index.docbook:6516
#, no-c-format
msgid "wildcard"
msgstr "jokertecken"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5295
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%artist]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%artist]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the artist that performed the corresponding block or "
"alternatively the author."
msgstr ""
"Ersätts med artisten som framförde motsvarande block, eller alternativt "
"kompositören."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5302 index.docbook:6559
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%title]</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>[%title]</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5303 index.docbook:6560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Will be replaced with the title of the block, which is taken from the "
"descriptive text of the label at the <emphasis>start</emphasis> of the "
"block. If that text is empty it will fall back to the title of the file (see "
"file information item \"<link linkend=\"INF_NAME\">Name</link>\"). If this "
"also does not exist, it will fall back to the base file name as described "
"above."
msgstr ""
"Ersätts med blockets rubrik, som tas från den beskrivande texten från "
"etiketten <emphasis>i början</emphasis> på blocket. Om texten är tom, "
"återgår den till filens rubrik (se filinformationsobjektet \"<link linkend="
"\"INF_NAME\">Namn</link>\"). Om den inte heller finns, återgår den till "
"basfilnamnet som beskrivs ovan."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example: <quote><command><literal>[%title] ([%artist])</literal></command></"
"quote> will detect author <quote><command><literal>Beethoven</literal></"
"command></quote> and title <quote><command><literal>Symphony No. 5</"
"literal></command></quote> from the string <quote><command><literal>Symphony "
"No. 5 (Beethoven)</literal></command></quote>."
msgstr ""
"Exempel: <quote><command><literal>[%title] ([%artist])</literal></command></"
"quote> detekterar kompositören <quote><command><literal>Beethoven</literal></"
"command></quote> titeln <quote><command><literal>Symfoni nr. 5</literal></"
"command></quote> från strängen <quote><command><literal>Symfoni nr. 5 "
"(Beethoven)</literal></command></quote>."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5327 index.docbook:6644
#, no-c-format
msgid "selection only"
msgstr "bara markering"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5334 index.docbook:5388 index.docbook:5509 index.docbook:5601
#: index.docbook:5800 index.docbook:6028 index.docbook:6348 index.docbook:6597
#: index.docbook:6651 index.docbook:6729 index.docbook:6865 index.docbook:7062
#: index.docbook:7129
#, no-c-format
msgid "value"
msgstr "värde"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5340 index.docbook:5394 index.docbook:5515 index.docbook:5607
#: index.docbook:5806 index.docbook:6034 index.docbook:6603 index.docbook:6657
#: index.docbook:6735 index.docbook:7068 index.docbook:7135
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>0</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>0</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5341 index.docbook:6658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save all sections of the whole file."
msgstr "Spara alla sektioner i hela filen."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5346 index.docbook:5401 index.docbook:5519 index.docbook:5611
#: index.docbook:5813 index.docbook:6041 index.docbook:6611 index.docbook:6663
#: index.docbook:6739 index.docbook:7072 index.docbook:7076 index.docbook:7139
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;<command>1</command>"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;<command>1</command>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5347 index.docbook:6664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Save only the sections that are within the current selection. If nothing is "
"selected, the whole file will be saved."
msgstr ""
"Spara bara sektioner som är inom aktuell markering. Om ingenting är markerat "
"sparas hela filen."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5361
#, no-c-format
msgid "project file"
msgstr "projektfil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name of the K3b project file, which will also be used as the base name "
"for the exported file names."
msgstr ""
"Namnet på K3b-projektfilen, som också kommer att användas som basnamn för de "
"exporterade filnamnen."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5371 index.docbook:6635
#, no-c-format
msgid "export location"
msgstr "exportplats"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5373
#, no-c-format
msgid "The location where the blocks should be saved."
msgstr "Platsen där blocken ska sparas."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: index.docbook:5380
#, no-c-format
msgid "overwrite policy"
msgstr "överskrivningsprincip"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5382 index.docbook:6591
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determines where the numbering should start."
msgstr "Bestämmer var numreringen ska starta."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5395 index.docbook:6612
#, no-c-format
msgid "Always start with index 1, with the risk of overwriting existing files."
msgstr "Börja alltid med index 1, med risk att befintliga filer skrivs över."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:5402 index.docbook:6604
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Continue after the index of the highest index that already exists, this "
"avoids overwriting existing files."
msgstr ""
"Fortsätt efter det största index som redan finns. Det undviker att "
"befintliga filer skrivs över."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5422
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo; (File Info)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo; (File Info)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the File Info Plugin"
msgstr "Skärmbild av insticksmodulen för filinformation"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5437
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_fileinfo;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a dialog window to view and change parameters and meta data of the "
"currently opened file. See section <link linkend=\"fileinfo\" endterm="
"\"title_fileinfo\"></link> in this manual."
msgstr ""
"Tillhandahåller ett dialogfönster för att visa och ändra parametrar och "
"metadata för filen som för närvarande är öppen. Se avsnittet <link linkend="
"\"fileinfo\" endterm=\"title_fileinfo\"></link> i handboken."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:5458
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_goto; (Goto Position)"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_goto; (Goto Position)"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:5466
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Goto Position Plugin"
msgstr "Skärmbild av insticksmodulen Gå till position"

#. Tag: literal
#: index.docbook:5473
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-plugin_goto;"
msgstr "&no-i18n-plugin_goto;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:5482
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows a dialog with the possibility to set the current position of the "
"selection to a new value, either by a time in milliseconds, by a position in "
"samples or by percentage of the length of the current file."
msgstr ""
"Visar en dialogruta med möjlighet att ställa in aktuell position för "
"markeringen till ett nytt värde, antingen med en tid i millisekunder, en "
"position i samplingar eller ett procentvärde av den aktuella filens längd."

#. Tag: replaceable
