#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:7782
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Info"
msgstr "Filinformation"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:7783
#, no-c-format
msgid "List of File Info Identifiers"
msgstr "Lista över identifierare i filinformation"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7788
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyword"
msgstr "Nyckelord"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7788
#, no-c-format
msgid "&#x0020;"
msgstr "&#x0020;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7788
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Beskrivning"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7793
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Album"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Album"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7794
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Name of the album if the source is an album that consist of more medias."
msgstr "Namnet på albumet om källan är ett album som består av flera medier."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7800
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Annotation"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Annotation"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7801 index.docbook:7871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides general comments about the file or the subject of the file. If the "
"comment is several sentences long, end each sentence with a period. Do not "
"include newline characters!"
msgstr ""
"Ger allmänna kommentarer om filen eller filens innehåll. Om kommentaren är "
"flera meningar lång, avsluta varje mening med en punkt. Inkludera inte "
"nyradstecken."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7808
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Archival location"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Archival location"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7809
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indicates where the subject of the file is archived."
msgstr "Anger var filens innehåll är arkiverat."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7814
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Author"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Author"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7815
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifies the name of the author of the original subject of the file. "
"Example: <quote>van Beethoven, Ludwig</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Identifierar namnet på upphovsmannen till filens ursprungliga innehåll. "
"Exempel: <quote>van Beethoven, Ludwig</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7821
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Lower Bitrate"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Lower Bitrate"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7822
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the lower limit in a VBR bitstream."
msgstr "Anger undre gränsen i en bitström med variabel bithastighet."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7827
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Bitrate Mode"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Bitrate Mode"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bitrate Mode (ABR, VBR, CBR, &etc;)"
msgstr ""
"Bithastighetstyp (genomsnittlig - ABR, variabel - VBR, konstant - CBR, etc.)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7833
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Bitrate"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Bitrate"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Nominal bitrate of the audio stream in bits per second"
msgstr "Ljudströmmens nominella bithastighet i bitar per sekund"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7839
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Upper Bitrate"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Upper Bitrate"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7840
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the upper limit in a VBR bitstream."
msgstr "Anger övre gränsen i en bitström med variabel bithastighet."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7845
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Bits per Sample"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Bits per Sample"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7846
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specifies the number of bits per sample."
msgstr "Anger antal bitar per sampling."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7851
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;CD"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;CD"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7852
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of the CD, if the source is an album of more CDROMs"
msgstr "Cd-nummer, om källan är ett album med fler än en cd-rom"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7857
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;CDS"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;CDS"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7858
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of CDs, if the source is an album of more CDROMs"
msgstr "Antal cd, om källan är ett album med fler än en cd-rom"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7863
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Commissioned"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Commissioned"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lists the name of the person or organization that commissioned the subject "
"of the file."
msgstr ""
"Listar namnet på personen eller organisationen som beställde filens innehåll."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7870
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Comments"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Comments"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7878
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Compression"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Compression"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7879
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sets a mode for compressing the audio data to reduce disk space."
msgstr ""
"Anger en metod för komprimering av ljuddata för att reducera diskutrymme."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7885
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Contact"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Contact"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7886
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contact information for the creators or distributors of the track. This "
"could be a URL, an email address, the physical address of the producing "
"label."
msgstr ""
"Kontaktinformation för skaparna eller distributörerna av spåret. Det kan "
"vara en webbadress, en e-postadress, eller den fysiska adressen till "
"skivbolaget."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7893
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Copyright"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Copyright"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7894
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Records the copyright information for the file. If there are multiple "
"copyrights, separate them by a semicolon followed by a space. Example: "
"<quote>Copyright Linux community 2002</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Lagrar filens copyright-information. Om det finns flera sådana, skilj dem åt "
"med ett semikolon följt av ett mellanslag. Exempel: <quote>Copyright Linux-"
"gemenskapen 2002</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7901
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Copyrighted"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Copyrighted"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7902
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indicates whether the file is protected by copyright or not."
msgstr "Anger om filen är skyddad av upphovsrätt eller inte."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7907
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Date"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Date"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7908
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the date the subject of the file was created. Example: "
"<quote>2001-12-24</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Anger datum filens innehåll skapades. Exempel: <quote>2001-12-24</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7914
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Engineer"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Engineer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7915
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Shows the name of the engineer who worked on the file. If there are multiple "
"engineers, separate the names by a semicolon and a blank."
msgstr ""
"Visar namnet på ingenjören som arbetade med filen. Om det finns flera "
"ingenjörer, skilj namnen åt med ett semikolon och ett mellanslag."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7922
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Estimated Length"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Estimated Length"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7923
#, no-c-format
msgid "Estimated length of the file in samples"
msgstr "Filens uppskattade längd i samplingar"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7928
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Filename"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Filename"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7929
#, no-c-format
msgid "Name of the opened file"
msgstr "Namn på den öppnade filen"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7934
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;File Size"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;File Size"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7935
#, no-c-format
msgid "Size of the file in bytes"
msgstr "Filens storlek i byte"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7940
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Genre"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Genre"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7941
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Describes the genre or style of the original work. Examples: <quote>classic</"
"quote>, <quote>pop</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Beskriver originalverkets genre eller stil. Exempel: <quote>klassiskt</"
"quote>, <quote>pop</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7947
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;ISRC"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;ISRC"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISRC number for the track; see the ISRC intro page for more information on "
"ISRC numbers. &url_isrc;"
msgstr ""
"Spårets ISRC-nummer. Se introduktionssidan för ISRC för mer information om "
"ISRC-nummer. &url_isrc;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7955
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Keywords"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Keywords"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7956
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Provides a list of keywords that refer to the file or subject of the file."
msgstr ""
"Tillhandahåller en lista med  nyckelord som hör ihop med filen eller dess "
"innehåll."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7962
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Labels"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Labels"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7963
#, no-c-format
msgid "The list of labels/markers."
msgstr "Listan med markörer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7968
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Length"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Length"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7969
#, no-c-format
msgid "Length of the file in samples."
msgstr "Filens längd i samplingar."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7974
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;License"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;License"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7975
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"License information, &eg;, <quote>All Rights Reserved</quote>, <quote>Any "
"Use Permitted</quote>, an URL to a license or the Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 "
"International (<quote>distributed under the terms of the Attribution-"
"ShareAlike 4.0 International License. See &url_cc_by_sa_4; for details</"
"quote>), &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Licensinformation, exempelvis <quote>Alla rättigheter reserverade</quote>, "
"<quote>Fri användning tillåten</quote>, en webbadress till en licens eller "
"Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (<quote>distribuerad enligt "
"villkoren i Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License. Se "
"&url_cc_by_sa_4; för detaljerad information</quote>), etc."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7985
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Medium"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Medium"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7986
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Describes the original subject of the file, where it was first recorded. "
"Example: <quote>orchestra</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Beskriver filens ursprungliga innehåll, där det först spelades in. Exempel: "
"<quote>orkester</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7992
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Mime Type"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Mime Type"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7993
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mime type of the file format"
msgstr "Filformatets Mime-typ"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7998
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Emphasis"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Emphasis"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:7999
#, no-c-format
msgid "Audio emphasis mode"
msgstr "Ljudets förbetoningsmetod"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8004
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Layer"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Layer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8005
#, no-c-format
msgid "MPEG Layer, I, II or III"
msgstr "MPEG-lager, I, II eller III"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8010
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Mode Extension"
msgstr " &no-i18n-tag;Metodutökning"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8011
#, no-c-format
msgid "MPEG Mode Extension (only if Joint Stereo)"
msgstr "MPEG-metodutökning (bara för gemensam stereo)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8016 index.docbook:8144
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Version"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Version"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8017
#, no-c-format
msgid "MPEG Version, 1, 2 or 2.5"
msgstr "MPEG-version, 1, 2 eller 2.5"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8022
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Name"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Name"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8023
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stores the title of the subject of the file. Example: <quote>Symphony No.6, "
"Op.68 &quot;Pastoral&quot;</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Lagrar titeln för filens innehåll. Exempel: <quote>Symfoni Nr. 6, Op. 68 "
"&quot;Pastoral&quot;</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8029
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Opus Frame Length"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Opus Frame Length"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8030
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Opus Frame Length in ms (supported values are 2.5, 5, 10, 20, 40, or 60 ms)"
msgstr ""
"Opus-ramlängd i ms (värden som stöds är 2,5, 5, 10, 20, 40 eller 60 ms)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8036
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Organization"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Organization"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8037
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Name of the organization producing the track (i.e. the <quote>record label</"
"quote>)"
msgstr ""
"Namn på organisationen som skapat spåret (dvs. <quote>skivbolaget</quote>)"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8043
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Original"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Original"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8044
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indicates whether the file is an original or a copy"
msgstr "Anger om filen är ett original eller en kopia"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8049
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Performer"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Performer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8050
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The artist(s) who performed the work. In classical music this would be the "
"conductor, orchestra, soloists. In an audio book it would be the actor who "
"did the reading."
msgstr ""
"Artist(er) som framför verket. För klassisk musik är det dirigenten, "
"orkestern, och solo-artister. För en ljudbok är det personen som läste in "
"boken."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8057
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Private"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Private"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8058
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indicates whether the subject is private"
msgstr "Anger om materialet är privat"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8063
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Product"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Product"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8064
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies the name or the title the file was originally intended for. "
"Example: <quote>Linux audio collection</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Anger namnet eller titeln som filen ursprungligen är avsedd för. Exempel: "
"&quot;Linux ljudsamling&quot;"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8070
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Sample Format"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Sample Format"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8071
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Format used for storing the digitized audio samples. Example: <quote>32-bit "
"IEEE floating-point</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Format använt för att lagra de digitaliserade ljudsamplingarna. Exempel: "
"<quote>32-bitars IEEE-flyttal</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8077
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Sample Rate"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Sample Rate"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8078
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of samples per second"
msgstr "Antal samplingar per sekund"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8083
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Software"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Software"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8084
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifies the name of the software package used to create the file. "
"Example: <quote>Kwave v0.6.4-1</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Identifierar namnet på programvarupaketet som användes för att skapa filen. "
"Exempel: <quote>Kwave v0.6.4-1</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8090
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Source"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Source"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8091
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifies the name of the person or organization who supplied the original "
"subject of the file. Example: <quote>Chaotic Sound Research</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Identifierar namn på personen eller organisationen som tillhandahöll filens "
"ursprungliga material. Exempel: <quote>Chaotic Sound Research</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8098
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Source form"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Source form"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8099
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifies the original form of the material that was digitized. Examples: "
"<quote>Record/Vinyl/90RPM</quote>, <quote>Audio DAT</quote>, <quote>tape/"
"CrO2/60min</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Identifierar materialets ursprungliga form som digitaliserades. Exempel: "
"<quote>skiva/vinyl/90 varv per minut</quote>, <quote>DAT-ljud</quote>, "
"<quote>band/CrO2/60 min</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8106
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Subject"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Subject"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Describes the subject of the file. Example: <quote>Bird voices at early "
"morning</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Beskriver filens innehåll. Exempel: <quote>Fågelsång en tidig morgon</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8113
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Technician"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Technician"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Identifies the technician who digitized the subject file. Example: "
"<quote>Torvalds, Linus</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Identifierar teknikern som digitaliserade filen. Exempel: <quote>Torvalds, "
"Linus</quote>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8120
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Track"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Track"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Track of the CD if the source was a CDROM."
msgstr "Spår på cd:n om källan är cd-rom."

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8126
#, no-c-format
msgid "&no-i18n-tag;Tracks"
msgstr "&no-i18n-tag;Tracks"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:8127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of tracks of the CD if the source was a CDROM."
msgstr "Antal spår på cd:n om källan är cd-rom."

#. Tag: entry
